EFF leader Julius Malema is accused of calling on his supporters to invade unoccupied land. JOHANNESBURG Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) leader Julius Malema's land invasion trial is expected to start in the Newcastle Regional Court in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday.Malema is accused of calling on his supporters to invade unoccupied land.It is understood a new charge has been brought against Malema which relates to the incitement to commit crime.The EFF leader has been charged twice under the Riotous Assemblies Act. In 2014, he allegedly called for land invasions during an elective conference in Bloemfontein.Malema also told his supporters in November last year to occupy any vacant land.This has since put the EFF leader in hot water, as he now faces charges of unlawfully and intentionally instigating his supporters to trespass and occupy land.The trial is set for two days in the Newcastle Regional Court.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)